review_text: The poor part of promenade st Hubert
Nothing special, just dirty subway station
Great place!
Cool station, BUT, if you go to the depanneur inside it, be careful because the guy is really shaddy and he tried to charge me 2$ on my stuff and not give me my bill...  Wich is illegal
Old and gloomy looking station.
Pretty clean, recently renovated metro entry and exit
Very clean.

(Translated by Google) The man at the counter was particularly rude, I couldn't pay at the machine so I asked him. he refused what I understand perfectly because he was closing his window so I ask him when he will open again to organize me and he writes on me as if I had harassed him.

(Original)
L’homme au guichet a été particulièrement désagréable, je ne pouvais pas payer à la machine alors je lui ai demandé. il a refusé ce que je comprends parfaitement car il fermait son guichet alors je lui demande quand il ouvrira à nouveau pour m’organiser et il me crit dessus comme si je l’avais harcelé.

(Translated by Google) The interior is a bit like a cave where you can take the orange line that takes you from the top of the city to the city center. Easy access to Plaza St-Hubert and located in Little Italy.

(Translated by Google) This is my neighborhood! I love it I fell in love with this borough, the living environment that it provides all in quality and diversity of choices of cultural activities businesses, green spaces and municipal services it offers to a population varied in terms of csp or diverse and mixed communities. In short it is really good to live ...

C est mon quartier ! Je l adore j ai eu un coup de coeur pour cet arrondissement, le cadre de vie qu'il procure tout en qualité et diversité de choix de commerces d'activités sociales culturelle, d espaces verts et services municipaux qu'il offre à une population variée  en terme de csp  ou de communautés diverses et mixtes.  Bref il y fait vraiment bon vivre ...
